    <a href="#" name="Rebate Strategies"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Rebate Strategies</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-list-ol" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-file-excel-o" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-envelope" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope out-of-scope">OUT OF SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        FSE, BMT and MMBP user roles negotiate Quarterly or Yearly Rebate Strategies in an offline Excel Spreadsheet.
        Most negotiations take months to complete while others must be completed withing 24 hours.
        The Rebate Strategies vary by customer and user with the potential of having hundreds of different Excel Formats.
    </p>
    <p>
        Typical tasks include grouping products together, comparing potential rebates to the Floor Price and running analytics to help in the decicion making process.
        All negotiations must both be coordinated with the customer as well as Intel's Geo and Division user base.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/rebatestrategies.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>


    <a href="#" name="Pricing Strategies"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Pricing Strategies</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-money" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-file-excel-o" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-envelope" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope out-of-scope">OUT OF SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        The Rebate Strategy focuses on Products and Pricing. The next step is to convert these Rebate Strategies into Pricing Strategies.
        The Pricing Strategy consists of Pricing Tables and Terms and Conditions about the Rebate Agreement.
        Currently this is a manualy conversion as decisions based on how payments will be made and the way the rebate was structure can dictate which potential Deal Type will be generated from the Pricing Table.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/pricingstrategy.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Pricing Table Association"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Pricing Table Association</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-table" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope in-scope">IN SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        The Pricing Tables should be created based on predefined Pricing Table Templates.
        These templates should map each field from the Pricing Table to Rebate Deal Attributes.
        The Pricing Table Template need to be managed in a secure admin tool.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/pricingassoc.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>




    <a href="#" name="Rebate Strategy Versions"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Rebate Strategy Versions</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-sort-numeric-asc" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-file-excel-o" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope out-of-scope">OUT OF SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        During the process of negotiating Rebate Stategies and creating Pricing Stratgies, back and forth communication with the Customer can result in many versions of the Rebate Strategy.
        Each Rebate Strategy needs to be saved because the customer might end up choosing an older version of the Rebate Strategy and the associated Meet Comp and Pricing Cost Tests run against that version.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/versions.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Rebate Strategy Approval"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Rebate Strategy Approval</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-refresh" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-cloud-download" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope in-scope">IN SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        FSE, BMT and MMBP user roles negotiate the Rebate Strategy.
        The system must track who and when the Rebate Strategy was approved for SOX compliance.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/approval.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Deal Validation"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Deal Validation</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-check-square-o" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-cloud-download" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope in-scope">IN SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        As the Rebate Strategy gets closer to completion, the resulting Draft Rebate Deals are Validated to ensure all necessary fields are populated.
        Some fields might be needed for Cost Test or DownStream Applications.
        The Deal Validation is managed by complex Business Logic that can "heal" common missing fields in the Deal.
        The deals can be validated in Bulk and pass or fail messages are queued and returned back to the client.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/validation.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Overlapping Deals"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Overlapping Deals</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-exchange" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-cloud-download" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope in-scope">IN SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        As the Draft Rebate Deals from the Pricing Strategies are prepared, the system needs to determine overlapping deals.
        Overlapping deals are defined by deals that overlap in time with the same products in such a way that it is possible for the customers to get multiple rebates for the same product.
        The overlapping rules should be managable from an admin screen.
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/overlapping.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Meet Comp Test"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Meet Comp Test</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-laptop" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-cloud-download" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope in-scope">IN SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        For certain products, Intel is required to ensure the product is NOT being sold for less than our competitors.
        Another reason for Meet Comp is to determine a reason for why a specific rate was requested.
    </p>
    <p>
        Meet Comp Test results are displayed on the screen with color indicators.
        <ul>
            <li><b>Green:</b> Meet Comp Passes</li>
            <li><b>Red:</b> Meet Comp Failes</li>
            <li><b>Yellow:</b> Incomplete Meet Comp due to required fields not being populated</li>
            <li><b>Grey:</b> Meet Comp is not needed</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/meetcomp.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Pricing Cost Test"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Pricing Cost Test</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-usd" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-briefcase" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-user" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-cloud-download" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px; ;"></i>
    </div>
    <div class="scope in-scope">IN SCOPE</div>
    <p>
        Pricing Cost Test is performed by MMBP against Product Cost data.
        The Cost Test must run against all overlapping deals in the current Rebate Strategy as well as any deal that has a tracker number.
        Based on the Product Group, Market Share and Standalone/Kit, various Cost Test formulas are computed against the Product Group to determine the Cost Test result.
    </p>
    <p>
        Cost Test results are displayed on the screen with color indicators.
        <ul>
            <li><b>Green:</b> Cost Test Passes</li>
            <li><b>Red:</b> Cost Test Failes</li>
            <li><b>Yellow:</b> Incomplete Cost Test due to required fields not being populated</li>
            <li><b>Grey:</b> Cost Test is not needed</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <div>
        <img src="/images/docs/costtest.png" style="margin-top: 10px;" />
    </div>



    <a href="#" name="Term and Conditions"></a>
    <h4 style="margin-top: 25px;">Term and Conditions</h4>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
        <i class="fa fa-legal" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 30px; color: #0071c5;"></i>
        <i class="fa fa-key" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 25px; color: #cccccc; margin-left: 5px;"></i>
